SIMPLE: irrecoverable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irrecoverable
<hw>Ir`re*cov"er*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not capable
of being recovered, regained, or remedied; irreparable; <as>as, an
<ex>irrecoverable</ex> loss, debt, or injury</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That which is past is gone and <qex>irrecoverable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Irreparable; irretrievable; irremediable;
unalterable; incurable; hopeless.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ir`re*cov"er*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Ir`re*cov"er*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irrecuperable</ent>⟦br⟧
